value.title: Unify The Enigma Community

value.description:
We propose increasing `slashing.signed_blocks_window` from 100 to 5000.

Currently `slashing.signed_blocks_window` is 100 and `slashing.min_signed_per_window` is 50%.
Therefore validators must sign at least 50 blocks out of the last 100 blocks to prevent being slashed because of downtime.
With the current block time of 5.76 seconds, validators cannot be offline for more than 4m48s.

If this proposal will pass:
Validators will be able to sign at least 2500 blocks out of the last 5000 blocks to prevent being slashed because of downtime.
Validators will be able to be offline for 4 hours at a time without being slashed, which will give more time for maintenance and chain updates.
value.title: Param Change slashing.signed_blocks_window: from 100 to 5000

value.description:
This proposal lays out the high level plan for Burn ENG for SCRT! SCRT (“Secret”) is used for staking, governance, and transaction fees within the Enigma network which is now LIVE based on Cosmos SDK/Tendermint. It is critical to the future of the Enigma protocol that the broader community that currently holds ENG tokens to be able to burn their tokens in exchange for SCRT being minted to participate in staking, governance, and transaction fees. This proposal will outline a brief background, technical approach, and detailed milestones to achieving an expeditious, straightforward and secure Burn ENG for SCRT!

value.description:
Update community fee

 This change is needed for community spend based proposals to be successfully funded.

 This proposal will change the current community tax from 2% to 75%.

 Once the community pool has enough funding to complete several existing/upcoming community spend based proposals, we will propose new fee/inflation settings for the Enigma Mainnet.

 Note:  While secretnodes.org will listen to feedback from all parties, understand that we are not a proxy for the team, community, or other validators, we will exclusively cast our vote for terms around fees/inflation that we believe best for the health of the network.

value.description: This network and its growth has been community-driven since launch, supported by many key contributors including, but extending far beyond, the Enigma core development team. The native coin of the network, essential for staking, governance, and value transfer, is Secret SCRT. The applications built on the network are Secret Applications, powered by Secret Contracts. The nodes helping to provide Layer 1 Privacy for the network are known as Secret Nodes. Given all of the above, this network should be referred to hereafter as Secret Network. Its continued growth and success should be regarded as resulting from our collective communal effort. Embracing this branding and realizing its full potential is only possible with the complete support of validators, developers, and community members in our ecosystem. Let us combine our efforts to grow the Secret Network, bring privacy to all people and all blockchains, and help achieve our shared mission of advancing privacy as a human right and public good.
value.title: Brand this network as Secret Network

value.description:
ChainofSecrets.org strongly believes in having adequate infrastructure, services & tools available for early adopters which provide a foundation for future growth and are essential to the greater Enigma Community.
 This Proposal provides Infrastructure that is integral for the Community and Developer Onboarding for Enigma network adoption. 

-----

The Enigma Blockchain and Secret Network requires a production stable testnet that all developers can use. 
 Testnets require constant maintenance and tweaking when actively developing an application you plan to deploy on the mainnet.

-----

You can view the Live Kamut Testnet Repo here: https://github.com/chainofsecrets/KamutBlockchain  

Here is our Github copy of the full proposal: https://github.com/chainofsecrets/docs/blob/master/The%20Testnet%20Proposal.pdf

value.description: The Romulus Upgrade Signal is to suggest a time to upgrade the Secret Network. This upgrade will rename the current enigma prefix to secret in order to rebrand the address format, additionally it will bring other improvements such as the addition of a new module. The proposed time for this upgrade is approximately 5am PT Wednesday June 10th 2020. The proposed time approximately corresponds to block 1,697,639 All additions can be reviewed in the following GitHub repo : https://github.com/secretnodes/secretnetwork. Any suggested or required changes to the repo must be made before June 7th. All official discussions around the Romulus Upgrade will be coordinated in the #the-romulus-upgrade room on https://chat.scrt.network
value.title: The Romulus Upgrade Signal

value.description: These changes modify the minimum & maximum inflation rate to 12%, makes the inflation change rate 0% so inflation is static, and changes the community tax rate to 20%, leaving 80% of rewards to validators. These changes are intended to make inflation easier to understand and staking more attractive. These changes are not necessarily intended to be permanent, we suggest future ammendments to the Secret Accords follow the suggested process outlined in the discussion here https://forum.scrt.network/t/the-secret-accords-proposal/1702
value.title: The Secret Accords
